Services: We utilize open source tools to create an application, including both a web and phone based interface. The Minimum Viable Product includes: Tour guide locator, Search features by city and region, Categories and recommended tours for art, music, food, sightseeing, historical events… Payment system, including customer service, Log in through other services such as Google, Facebook, and Twitter. Second and third generation updates to include: A built in one-stop-shop itinerary with sharable calendar, Linking tool to resources such as Expedia, Kayak, and Priceline, Push notifications, On-line chat rooms, Bundled destinations for economy travelers, Voice messaging for those less technologically inclined, (or people who have big thumbs, or less the optimal eye sight), Even more features and benefits to come… Become a Guide: We have two types of users; guides and travelers. Guides: creating job opportunities in the gig economy, fostering independence, a new life style and future career opportunity, taking care of family needs, flexible schedules… Whether you’d like to grow a full time self-employed business. Or use this as a side gig, we will help you grow independence and flexibility. Travelers: people who seek the unique experience in far off lands. People attracted to different cultures. Families wishing to bond in exotic locations. Individuals and couples seeking insight to native culture. Students on holiday, history buffs, art galleries, music venues, foodies, shopping, golf, etc.… Whether you’d like to grow a full time self-employed business. Or use this as a side gig, we will help you grow independence and flexibility.
